events.description: The release of Taiwan's annual inflation rate for January 2026, showing a significant slowdown.

facts.fact_text: Taiwan's annual inflation rate slowed to 0.69% in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: The annual inflation rate in Taiwan slowed to 0.69% in January 2026, sharply down from 1.31% in December

facts.fact_text: Inflation has remained below the central bank's 2% target for nine consecutive months.

evidences.evidence_text: This was also the ninth consecutive month below the central bank’s 2% target.

facts.fact_text: Transportation and communication costs experienced a deflation of 1.95%.

evidences.evidence_text: Downward pressures came from continued deflation in transportation and communication (-1.95% vs -1.34% in December)

facts.fact_text: Education and entertainment costs declined by 0.97%.

evidences.evidence_text: declines in education and entertainment costs (-0.97% vs 1.69%).

facts.fact_text: Seasonally adjusted monthly consumer prices rose by 0.10%.

evidences.evidence_text: On a seasonally adjusted monthly basis, consumer prices rose 0.10%, following a 0.14% gain in the previous month.

claims.claim_text: The January 2026 inflation rate is the lowest level since January 2021.

evidences.evidence_text: marking the lowest level since January 2021.
